-- China's CSI300 jumps as Beijing pledges to step up capital market reforms
-- By Yimou Lee and Grace Li
-- Sun May 11, 2014 11:35PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, May 12 (Reuters) - China's CSI300 index <.CSI300> climbed more than two percent in late morning trade on Monday, in its best day in more than a month, as Beijing pledged to push ahead with capital market reforms [ID:nB9N0LO02I].

Chinese banks and brokerages led gains in the CSI300 index, comprising of the leading Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings, pushing the index up to its biggest daily gain since April 8.